definition.value: A glycosyl galactose consisting of an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue and a beta-D-galactofuranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A 2,3-dihydroxybutanedioic acid that has meso configuration.

An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of a beta-D-xylofuranose residue, a beta-D-mannopyranose residue and two 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->2), (1->4) and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A tetraric acid that is butanedioic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3.
